The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Afghan blast
                                                                                                               Afghan blast
                            
	Mohammad Agha (Afghanistan), July 9 (Reuters): An explosion outside a school south of the Afghan capital today killed at least 25 people, including 15 students, officials said. They said it was caused by explosives hidden in the back of a truck which had crashed.                                                                                                                                                                              
